==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hobbler
<hw>Hob"bler</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. also <ets>hobeler</ets>, OF.
<ets>hobelier</ets>, LL. <ets>hobellarius</ets>. See <er>Hobby</er> a
horse.]</ety> <fld>(Eng. Hist.)</fld> <def>One who by his tenure was to
maintain a horse for military service; a kind of light horseman in the
Middle Ages who was mounted on a hobby.</def> <rj><au>Hallam. Sir J.
Davies.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

